title: Beautiful!
text: I had actually never heard of shungite before I came across this listing. That sparked my interest, and I had to learn more. Apparently, shungite is pretty rare and thus more expensive than most stones used for beaded bracelets. There is also a lot of fake shungite out there, so buyer beware. I believe the shungite in this bracelet is authentic due to several quick tests one can do. The bracelet is surprisingly lightweight, which surprised me, but that is supposed to be one of the attributes of shungite. It's also supposed to be antibacterial--how interesting is that? And it has protection qualities. I love the magnetic clasp, and unlike other customers, I've had no issues with mine. Based on my experience, I have to recommend.

title: Good for skin issues
text:
My son has skin issues and has the occasional outbreak, so I got this epsom salt/sea salt product for him to soak in. Epsom salt can be good for softening rough, dry skin, and exfoliating dead skin cells. It may also soothe skin affected by skin conditions, including eczema and psoriasis. He has psoriasis, we think, and it makes him miserable when it gets bad.

He's used the product a couple of times now, and he said his rash was receding somewhat and the itching was better. He said he just felt invigorated after a good, long soak. Doesn't hurt that this product also smells nice. However, he said for those who don't care for fragrance, it might be a little overpowering for some.

While I don't believe this is a cure for skin problems, I do think it can be one of the tools for controlling the worst of the symptoms. My son is pleased, and that's a win in my book.

And the loofah sponge in the bar is an application I haven't seen before. It's great for washing feet and anywhere I just want extra clean. I worried at first that the fibers would be too harsh to scrub with, but that wasn't the case. You do have to use the soap for several washings before the the sponge starts to appear. I've been using the bar daily for nearly a month now, and it's not even half gone. So it lasts awhile, which is good because, though not expensive, it's not cheap either. Definitely will buy again.

title: Lovely, subtle scents
text: These soaps and conditioner are clearly handmade and hand cut. They're lovely and would make a great gift. I like the vegan and eco-friendly aspect of all the bars. They are scented but not overly, which I appreciate. The body bar actually has lavender plant bits decorating the top. Nice touch. I've tried all three bars, but I don't usually use conditioner because my hair's too fine. It definitely softened my hair, though, and made it easier to comb. Shampoo bar is my absolute favorite of the three. It lathers well with a subtle fragrance, and looks like it will last quite a while. Which is good, because the only downside is the cost. It's a pricey set, but worth it if you are into organic and eco-friendly products. Which brings me to the packaging. A thin, cardboard paper box is used for each bar. Very little to throw away and biodegradable. That's a significant plus.

title: After two years...still looks new and perfect!!!
text:
After two years my flags still look brand new. Leaving this review as I came on here to order another set for my new truck. The installation issues others have can be negated for the most part by TAKING YOUR TIME and not rushing the installation.

Installation tips:
- All pieces are individual and will look out of place if you do not lay it flat to the glass...do not allow wrinkles to begin

- You must have clean and cool window glass before you start, use alcohol and do not touch the glass with bare skin

- Do NOT try installing this on a windy day or if there is a lot of particulates flying in the air such as a dusty day...it will be trapped behind the decal

- Use a plastic scrapper to apply even pressure as you roll it out

- If you get an air bubble...do not panic and try pulling it off the glass...the decal can rip. After you finish, use a blow dryer or heat gun on low to apply heat to the decal and use a stick pin to poke a hole in the air bubble

- Cut the sharp points of the stars to round out the stars legs a bit otherwise as the windows roll up and down they can grab and peel back a little...can be done before or after installation
